(49, 310, 'What is an SSL certificate and why should it have your site?', 'ssl-certificate', '<p><em> SSL certificates can be considered the basis of a secure Internet connection. But do you know what they are and why they are important to your website? What is an SSL certificate? SSL is an abbreviation for the English <em> Secure Sockets Layer Protocol , which is located between the transport layer and the application layer. This protocol (certificate) provides encrypted data transfer between your computer and the website or server to which you connect over the Internet. An SSL-secured connection protects by encrypting all transmitted data - such as payment data or your online communications. In addition to security, SSL also brings other benefits - one of them, for example, is better SEO in terms of search engines. The added value is also protection against basic types of cyber-attacks (especially man-in-the-middle) or credibility. Sites with a valid SSL certificate are marked with a green URL and lock icon in most browsers. They tell you about their security and make the visitors trust that their connection to this site will be safe. <em> A valid and properly set SSL certificate should be an elemental part of every website that takes care of itself and its visitors. How does an SSL connection work? An SSL connection is established between the server (website) and your browser using the "SSL handshake" process. When creating an encrypted connection, 3 digital (encryption) keys are used, as follows:</em></em></em></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The server sends a copy of your asymmetric public key to your browser.</li>\r\n<li>The browser creates a symmetric session key and encrypts the asymmetric public key of the server, which then sends the server back.</li>\r\n<li>The server decrypts the received key using its private asymmetric key to obtain a symmetric session key.</li>\r\n<li>The server and browser will establish a connection and all encrypted / decrypted data will be encrypted / decrypted using the session symmetry created. This is only used for one session and is no longer used after it.\r\n<p>With encrypted communication, a one-time symmetric encryption key is used, which only recognizes your browser and the server with which it communicates. This ensures the protection of transmitted data against a third party. What does a valid SSL certificate contain? A valid SSL certificate must contain some information. The basis is information about the publisher of the SSL certificate, which we call the general certification terminology for the <em> certification authority (CA). It should be an organization that the visitor (and if the CA and IT world is verified) trusts. In addition to CA information, the certificate should also include its serial number, expiration date (usually certificates are valid for 1-3 years), a copy of the certificate owner''s public key and the digital signature of the certification authority. Several parameters refer to the security level of the certificate. It is the standard to which it was created (eg X.509), the level of communication encryption it uses (eg, 256-bit cipher), the cryptographic method of making keys (eg RSA SHA-2 with 256-bit hash) and the encryption method keys (e.g., 2048-bit cipher). Certificates signed by the site owner In addition to SSL certificates issued by a publicly trusted certification authority, there is also the possibility to create a certificate signed by the website owner itself. We recommend using them only for private purposes and not for the purpose of linking your site and the public. A certificate issued by a private authority can be easily misused if the server administrator does not sufficiently protect its hidden part - the private key. Only the server administrator should have access to it. If a private key were acquired by someone other than the certificate issuer, they could use it to redirect data communications over their servers. Unsecured data decryption and their misuse (man-in-the-middle attack) could take place on them. If such an attack is also detected, it is not possible to invalidate a private certificate at a time earlier than its predetermined expiration. By using such a compromised certificate for public communications purposes, the company would be responsible for the possible escape of a large amount of sensitive data for its clients. What SSL certificate should I choose for my site? Different types of SSL certificates are available that offer a different level of security. In the base partition, we can distinguish between <em> domain validation, organization validation , or <em> extended validation certificate (EV). <em> <a href="https://cloudssl.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> </a> Types of certificates by number of secure domains In terms of domains and subdomains you need to secure, we also distinguish between 3 types of SSL certificates:</em></em></em></em></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><em> Single-name SSL certificateSecures an encrypted connection for one domain / subdomain. Such a certificate protects, for example, www.mojadomena.sk, but does not protect mail.mojadomena.sk.</em></li>\r\n<li><em> Wildcard SSL CertificateSecures an encrypted connection for 1 domain and any number of its subdomains. Such a certificate protects, for example, the website www.mojandomena.sk, but also mail.mojandomena.sk, blog.mojadomena.sk or other domena.domena.sk. In general, the SSL certificate protects all sites * .mojadomena.sk.</em></li>\r\n<li><em><em> Multi-domain (SAN) Subject SSL certificateThis certificate type allows an organization to protect up to 100 different domains in its ownership. For example, www.mojadomena.sk, www.mojadomena.org, mail.mojadomena.com, blog.mojadomena.co.uk, or any other domain under one certificate holder. This type of SSL certificate is used by international companies that use the same level 2 domain name in multiple first-level domains (such as Google and its domain * .google.com, * .google.com, ...).</em></em>\r\n<p><em> When selecting an SSL certificate, it is necessary to look at the security level as well as the number of domains you need to secure. And do not underestimate the choice of certification authority. In particular, look at the level of security in your certificates, the lifetime of their certificates, the compatibility of mobile devices, and how much you can trust your organization. A free option for securing your site is SSL certificates from LetsEncrypt, which offer automatic renewal and validity for 3 months. They also offer the ability to apply up to 100 SANs at DV level. LetsEncrypt plans to introduce wildcard SSL certificates soon to simplify the free provisioning of your websites. If you are not sure about your SSL certificate, feel free to contact us. We will be happy to assist you in selecting, setting up, and applying the certificate to any number of domains. </em></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '', 1, 23, '2018-12-05 19:28:21', 558, '', '2018-12-05 19:28:21', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2018-12-05 19:28:21', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"images\\/articles\\/64d93d666355a43c4a86679a030d35b6.jpg","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"article_layout":"","show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","info_block_show_title":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_associations":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_page_title":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":"","spfeatured_image":"","post_format":"standard","gallery":"","audio":"","video":"","link_title":"","link_url":"","quote_text":"","quote_author":"","post_status":""}', 1, 3, '', '', 1, 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, 'en-GB', '', ''),
(50, 311, 'Important changes to GDPR privacy', 'important-changes-to-gdpr-privacy', '<p><em> The new European Privacy Policy (GDPR) <em> has been in force since May 25, 2018. It brings a number of changes, including, in particular, testing online security environments or empowering people responsible for managing personal data.</em></em></p>\r\n<h3>consent to processing of personal data</h3>\r\n<p>If you own a website, an e-shop, or you are making an online questionnaire, you will surely have a check box to agree with the handling of personal information. Such a pre-checked consent will no longer be valid. With new processing of personal data, you will need to ask for new approvals. We also agree with the processing of your children''s personal data. For children under the age of 16, only the parent or their legal representative may grant consent. The new regulation specifies the terms of consent:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>consent must be free, specific, informed, and unambiguous</li>\r\n<li>consent must be given for a specific purpose, for each purpose, each must be named</li>\r\n<li>Acknowledgment must be as easy as giving consent\r\n<h3 p="">Expand and refine the rights of individuals to better control personal data. These include, for example, the right to:</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>information</li>\r\n<li>access to personal information</li>\r\n<li>patch</li>\r\n<li>Erase / Forget - This right follows on from the older "right to erase". For example, an individual may apply it if the data is unlawfully processed or has opted out of consent to the processing of personal data.\r\n<p><em> "Clients will have the right to delete or move personal data from your database."</em></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Right to Restrict Processing</li>\r\n<li>Right to data portability - The person concerned will have the right to transfer his / her personal data to another operator. The original operator is required to provide this data in the normal format. An example is the change of the mobile operator. If the user decides to transfer his number to another operator after May 25, 2018, the original operator must provide the new operator of the user with personal data (their type directly governed by the Regulation) associated with the use of his services during the provision of the service.</li>\r\n<li>Right to object</li>\r\n<li>Right to object profiling\r\n<h3>Safety precautions</h3>\r\n<p>When processing personal data, you are responsible for their security against cyber attacks. Your obligation will take reasonable precautions, for example:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>pseudonymization</li>\r\n<li>encryption</li>\r\n<li>Ensure the continued confidentiality, integrity and availability of systems / services</li>\r\n<li>Ability to restore the availability of personal data in the event of an incident in time\r\n<h3>Regular security testing</h3>\r\n<p>An important security measure will also be regular testing and assessment of the effectiveness of the security measures taken to ensure data processing security (eg <a href="https://citadelo.sk/sluzby/audity-bezpecnosti/"> Penetration Tests </a> &gt;, <a href="https://hacktrophy.com/preco-je-dolezity-bug-bounty-program-pre-stredne-firmy/"> bug bounty programs </a>). This measure also includes checking the security of the application or site through which personal data flows. For companies, it means they have to pay attention to how they have a coded site and whether it does not contain security holes through which it can be hacked and stolen. <em> If you do not know if your site or mobile app is safe enough, test it with ethical hackers from <a href="https://citadelo.com/"> Citadelo </a> or &lt; a href = "https://hacktrophy.com/"&gt; <em> hacktrophy.com <em>.</em></em></em></p>\r\n<h3>Documentation</h3>\r\n<p>Once you are new, you must comply with the protection of personal data. It is your duty to show how this requirement is complied with. Therefore, it is essential to have the necessary documentation available, for example:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>internal guidelines (attendance, file handling, incident identification, camera system, e-mail, backup)</li>\r\n<li>documenting the security measures taken</li>\r\n<li>staff training on personal data processing obligations\r\n<h3>Notification obligation introduced</h3>\r\n<p>Each operator and intermediary will be obliged to report any incident, ie a breach of personal data protection, within 72 hours of the Office of Personal Data Protection of the Slovak Republic. In the event of an incident and possible theft of personal data, he will be obliged to report the incident to the person concerned. Another change is the obligation to document cases of personal data breach and the need to submit them to the Office upon request. Everyone who processes personal information should answer the following questions:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Can you detect an incident and a privacy violation early?</li>\r\n<li>Can you properly and timely evaluate the incident, its consequences and take action?\r\n<h3>Will a person be responsible?</h3>\r\n<p>If you process a large amount of personal data or are sensitive data, you are definitely responsible (may be a legal entity). We surely recommend that you:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>have an internal analysis of whether or not the responsible person should be named and show that you have taken all relevant factors into account</li>\r\n<li>entrusted within your organization with a person who will have privacy protection "in the job description"\r\n<p>For violation of GDPR''s obligations, a fine of up to € 20 million or 4% of total turnover for the previous financial year (whichever is greater) is a penalty. Likewise, any person who has suffered harm as a result of a violation of the Regulation is entitled to compensation. The application of the new GDPR Regulation thus significantly increases the demand for Slovak and Czech companies. Companies are under new obligation to test the security of online systems through which personal data is moving. Companies should have an overview of the flow of personal data and periodically review, assess and evaluate the effectiveness and appropriateness of the security measures that are taken.</p>\r\n<h3 ul=""></h3>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Identify which personal data you have / process in your business, and whether you process it legally and for the purpose for which it was obtained.</li>\r\n<li>Answer the question which data you really need; Do not delete and delete unnecessary data.</li>\r\n<li>Identify the flow of personal information in your organization - how and where it is stored, protected or deleted, and who has access to it.\r\n<h3>Are you ready?</h3>\r\n<p>Prepare legal, personnel and technical conditions for implementing the regulation can be challenging for many companies. So do not hesitate to contact external companies that are working on the issue and delegate these tasks to them.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '', 1, 25, '2018-12-05 19:29:15', 558, '', '2018-12-05 19:39:38', 558, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2018-12-05 19:29:15', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"images\\/articles\\/ccb4e23c8aa216f1e96d31ab209c036b.jpg","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"article_layout":"","show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","info_block_show_title":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_associations":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits"