(51, 312, 'IOT Business Hub', 'iot-bussiness-hub', '<h3>Your Business Performance Efficiency Tool</h3>\r\n<p>At present, commercial companies have already discovered the amazing added value of new technologies like IoT or Big Data Analysts. The incentives for using these technologies are opportunities that are already able to offer a strong added value for business. First, they enable our customers to save costs, thereby indirectly increasing profits. No less significant added value is to increase the efficiency of processes, where the technology used can help simplify processes or change them to bring added value either directly to the company or to its customers. IoT technology is to be understood only as a means of collecting valuable data about some business entities. In the second step, accurate data collection is supported by specialized data analysis based on the results of IoT devices. For analytical purposes and business optimization suggestions, we have dedicated ourselves to Big Data (for example, scientific research on a large amount of data). For a specific understanding of the use we can offer a solution for IoT technology for your business that we have developed to manage and route the data flow according to specific ideas and requirements of tailor-made customers.</p>\r\n<p>This project has already been implemented and deployed with our specific customer for thousands of devices. After designing the technical solution, we also help clients with the evaluation and processing of raw data in the form of structured feedback and detailed data analysis. The basic framework of applications that make up the IoT SW solution is as follows: The primary objective of the SW solution is to provide business partner data for business entities. the advantage of our solution is that it does not oblige the partner to use specific network technology. It even allows information about the same type of business entity to be delivered in parallel from different IoT networks (by coverage, convenience of contracts, etc.). solution it also allows information sent from different IoT transmitters of one IoT network to be registered to different partners. The SW solution consists of separate pre-integrated components that communicate through defined interfaces. The IOT Partner Business Hub application is intended to separate CRM (business functionality) from proprietary network communication - that is, allows you to attach business applications to so-called "Business API," or connect a new network (network type) without affecting the business app.</p>\r\n<p>The independence of business parts from the network provider and the specificity of the network technology used is achieved. In the case of upgrading or changes to support another network, it is enough to change the Partner Business Hub component. The basic entity in the Partner Business Hub is the IoT transmitter with its serial number (EUI) which uses the IoT network server to send messages. Messages such as signal strength, shipment time, receiving GTW, message size, unambiguous management identifier, and business information (generally a sensor or sensor state) in the base64 / hexa format are metainformations. It is important to note that network management Typically, the business entity identifier does not have to be the absolute state of a business entity (for example, the state of a meter), and the business content of the message may not be a business entity identifier (customer, number of the meter, location number, etc.). For example, in the case of smart meters in utility companies, the number of pulses recorded by the sensor since it is mounted on the consumption meter - i.e., The application in its database contains mapping of IoT transmitters to a business entity, including the attributes needed to convert the sensor / sensor state to relevant business information.</p>', '', 1, 25, '2018-12-05 19:30:08', 558, '', '2018-12-05 19:30:08', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2018-12-0