(52, 313, 'Best Cloud Storage for Your Files', 'cloud-storage', '<p>Storage is never enough. Although we can easily expand the capacity of our computer with increasingly larger internal, external drives or USB keys, the more popular alternative today is the cloud that offers data independently of the platform and simple sharing capabilities, although in most cases at the expense of privacy. Unlike physical data carriers, the cloud offers multiple benefits. We do not have to worry about the data coming through the physical media error, but we have access to it from anywhere and from any device if we have a fast and stable internet connection. If circumstances so require, we can also download individual data to the device so we can access them even if we are not connected to the Internet. We have a choice from a wide portfolio of cloud solutions, and everyone can choose from their preferences. Almost every service offers a free version, but if we are interested in higher capacities, we do not avoid monthly charges.</p>\r\n<h3>Dropbox</h3>\r\n<p>Dropbox is a fast-paced, cloud-based solution that is simplicity and reliability. He will also be pleased with its broad support and the ability to install an application on all popular operating systems, whether on computers or smartphones. Applications are very well-crafted, clear, and easy to share files quickly. The company has also recently launched the Paper Service to create notes or documents, and is directly linked to Dropbox. The main drawback of Dropbox is the small storage size in the free version. If you do not want to pay, count only 2 GB of space. For 9.99 euros per month or 99 euros a year, you can subscribe to 1 TB of free space. The company also offers solutions for teams where it is possible to get from 15 euros per month unlimited space. However, it is necessary to expect that the data is stored in the United States and unencrypted.</p>\r\n<h3>Google Drive</h3>\r\n<p>If you already have a Google Account, you have access to the Google Drive cloud automatically. As a Google product, Drive is strongly integrated with most of Google''s services. Google Docs created in Sheets, Docs, Slides are all centrally available on Drive Drive, making it easy for the user to manage and share them. You can also easily save attachments from Gmail and enjoy the integration of Google Photos. Drive shares its storage with Gmail and data from your Google Photos, so the available capacity is shared between all services. In the free version Google offers 15 GB of space for your files. If you are 15GB a little, but you do not need the whole terabyte at the same time, there is the possibility to subscribe to a 100GB storage for 1.99 euros per month or, respectively, 19.99 for advance payment for the whole year. One TB space costs € 9.99 per month or € 99.99 per year. The most you can subscribe to 30 TB for EUR 299.99 per month. Of course, Windows, MacOS as well as Android and iOS applications are commonplace. Even in this case, the data is stored in the US and unencrypted.</p>\r\n<h3>OneDrive</h3>\r\n<p>Microsoft software giant also offers custom software storage. OneDrive is part of the latest Windows 10 operating system, but the native application is also available for OSX and Windows Phone, Android, and iOS mobile platforms. OneDrive is a good choice if you also prefer other Microsoft products as it does not have a good connection with the cloud office suite MS Office 365. Based on Microsoft, it offers 5 GB of free storage, and for 2 euros a month it is possible to subscribe to 50 GB of cloud space. There is also no option to subscribe to 1 TB solution for 7 euros per month or more. 69 eur per year, with the MS Office 365 service license included in this package. Again, data is stored in the US and unencrypted.</p>\r\n<h3>iCloud</h3>\r\n<p>Apple platform users have the option to use iCloud, which is directly integrated into macOS and iOS. The advantage of iCloud is especially true if you own multiple devices from Apple and you can easily synchronize data between them through iCloud. Compatibility with other platforms is all the worse. Apple has 5 GB of storage for free use and 99GB a month for 50GB of storage. Next is 200GB for 2.99 euros per month and 2TB for 9.99 euros per month. Data is stored in the US and only a part is encrypted.</p>\r\n<h3>Mega</h3>\r\n<p>For those who want the largest storage in the free version, Mega is the right service for Kim Dotcom, the author of the controversial canceled Megaupload service. In the free version, the Mega user offers up to 50GB of data. The service does not lack rich sync capabilities, the Windows, MacOS and Linux apps as well as the mobile operating system versions. You can also use Meg as an extension for Chrome and Firefox. Mega is the only service in this article that has data encrypted on your servers with keys that you only have as owners of the data. The Mega service does not know what data you have in the cloud and can be considered the only one that does not disturb your privacy. If you do not have enough 50 GB, you can buy 200 GB of space per month at a price of 4.99 euros, with 1 TB worth the same competition of 9.99 euros. There are also 4 and 8 TB spaces in the menu.</p>\r\n<h3>box</h3>\r\n<p>The Cloud Storage Box tries to target mainly businesses and business users, but it can also appeal to individuals. The service also offers applications for all major operating systems, and will also be pleased with integration with many other services and applications. The box also gives the user a lot of privacy control. Free storage offers the user 10GB of space, and for 8euro per month, it is possible to subscribe to 100GB, which is somewhat higher compared to the competitor.</p>\r\n<h3>Custom Cloud</h3>\r\n<p>One option is also to set up your own cloud. For example, solutions from Synology are popular. Just buy a NAS with the disk capacity you prefer, and you no longer pay for it, as is the case with standard cloud services. The advantage of your own solution is that you know where your data is and you have privacy. Even home solutions do not have access to multiple devices or automatic backup of photos, and we can also find similarities to Sheets, Docs, or more. To some extent, there is no connection with the cloud of well-known players in the market.</p>', '', 1, 25, '2018-12-05 19:31:18', 558, '', '2018-12-05 19:44:55', 558, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2018-12-05 19:31:18', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"images\\/articles\\/37a06e4a72d6cb27621f1ed829bbee81.jpg","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"article_layout":"","show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","info_block_show_title":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_associations":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_page_title":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":"","spfeatured_image":"","post_format":"standard","gallery":"","audio":"","video":"","link_title":"","link_url":"","quote_text":"","quote_author":"","post_status":""}', 2, 1, '', '', 1, 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, 'en-GB', '', ''),
(53, 314, 'How to prepare for GDPR?', 'how-to-prepare-for-gdpr', '<p>Peter Fuska, CEO of Digmia, about what will bring the new GDPR regulation to individuals and businesses, what does that mean in practice and how companies can prepare for it. Please read the interview or watch the video.</p>\r\n<h3>What changes does the new OU do for businesses? h3&gt;</h3>\r\n<p>The new EU Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) enters into force uniformly throughout the EU on 25 May 2018. The Regulation provides for increased protection of individuals in the processing of personal data, in particular by entrepreneurs and public administrations and self-governments. For natural persons, this extends the scope of the rights they may apply to the processing of personal data, such as the right to transfer personal data, the limitation of processing or the complete deletion of personal data. Similarly, entrepreneurs and institutions (whether in the position of an operator or an intermediary) introduce obligations that an entrepreneur has to meet if a natural person wants to exercise his rights in the area of ​​personal data protection.</p>\r\n<h3>What specific principles or principles of protection the OU brings and what does it mean in practice?</h3>\r\n<p>The Regulation defines eight principles that will govern the processing of personal data of the individuals concerned. I will only mention the key: the principle of legality and purpose limitations, we can obtain personal information only for a specific purpose and process it only in a way that is compatible for that purpose. For the purpose of defining the purpose, the entrepreneur has either support in other laws (eg the Social / Health Insurance Act when collecting OU when reporting a worker to a social or health insurance company) or processing necessary for performance of the contract or for pre-contractual arrangements (eg when buying a holiday or tickets) or there is a legitimate interest of the businessman in processing (eg, the protection of his / her own property when entering the premises). Of course, personal data can be processed based on the consent of the natural person, which in many cases will be the only legal solution. The principle of minimization in terms of the extent and duration of the retention of personal data, the entrepreneur has to check, for example, for the purpose of the selection process, only collects the data relevant for decision-making on candidates and will not be able to keep the resumes of unsuccessful candidates for a long time after the selection and occupation of the position (many managers will find such CVs in their emails or folders). The principle of integrity and confidentiality, the entrepreneur must have adequate technical means and measures in place to ensure the security of personal data and to prevent unauthorized access, damage or loss of personal data.</p>\r\n<p>There is a fairly wide range of technical means, I would certainly start with areas where there is a high level of vulnerability - PC protection, especially laptops, that workers normally transfer between work and home. Introducing disk encryption on your laptop is key to data protection in case of theft. It is also important to protect data in the electronic data transfer between company headquarters and external parties - transmission via an encrypted VPN tunnel as a necessity for personal data to be captured and misused. Managing employee access to personal data is particularly important in minimizing personal data misuse inside the company. It is recommended to introduce a 2-factor authentication that requires additional authentication of the person accessing personal data (eg token) in addition to logins and passwords.</p>\r\n<h3>. to lose or steal personal data, what steps do you need on the operator side?</h3>\r\n<p>At first it is important to judge how high the likelihood that theft, the laptop will lead to a high risk from the point of view of the rights of the individuals concerned. If a doctor stole a notebook with an unencrypted disk that has sensitive patient health data, the risk is high and the operator is required to report an incident to the Office for Personal Data Protection within 72 hours of its occurrence. It is also necessary to inform the affected person of such breach / incidents. In order to communicate with the Authority and the persons concerned, it is appropriate to have a so- responsible person. However, not every operator must necessarily have such a person - it concerns, for example, public authorities or processors who process specific categories of data such as genetic, biometric, health, and so on.</p>\r\n<h3>The new Regulation enters into force on 25 May 2018. How are entrepreneurs and institutions prepared and what do you need to do to comply with this regulation?</h3>\r\n<p>Many, in particular, small and medium-sized businesses have been convinced that the regulation does not concern them, or they intervene very marginally, and that''s why they did not get them. However, when we realize that personal data is most often a part of customer and employee data (every entrepreneur has customers and the vast majority also employs individuals), the regulation can not be avoided. In terms of readiness, most entrepreneurs are in the first - analytical phase in which they identify where processes / functional areas are or are not in line with the Regulation. The part (rather minority) has a ready-made implementation plan and has begun introducing measures for critical areas. To achieve compliance, each processor should have at least three basic steps:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Perform a so-called GAP analysis, i. view your business processes, map your personal data flowing through the organization, and assess where the areas do not meet the requirements of the regulation (eg to assess or have a purpose for collecting and processing personal data)</li>\r\n<li>Prepare a draft measure, evaluate it in terms of cost and time, and create an implementation plan</li>\r\n<li>Run the implementation of steps that can cover the areas of: o Technical (IT) - encryption, pseudonymization, 2-factor authentication and others o Organizational - change of scope of collected personal data in processes, modifications in the entitlements of personnel processing personal data or change physical access to premises where sensitive personal information is processed. o Legal and documentation - preparation of texts for consent to the processing of personal data, preparation and signing of processing contracts with business partners, eventually introducing a code of conduct, etc.</li>\r\n</ul>', '', 1, 25, '2018-12-05 19:32:16', 558, '', '2018-12-05 19:40:16', 558, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2018-12-05 19:32:16', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"images\\/articles\\/542390225756f78888142d54f3d17e01.jpg","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"article_layout":"","show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","info_block_show_title":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_associations":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_page_title":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":"","spfeatured_image":"","post_format":"standard","gallery":"","audio":"","video":"","link_title":"","link_url":"","quote_text":"","quote_author":"","post_status":""}', 2, 0, '', '