still not in production when your work report is longer than 500 scraped toilet paper.</p>\r\n<h3>What does OpenStack do?</h3>\r\n<p>At this point, it''s time to tell what it''s all about doing. Stay on the ground and avoid answering everything. You need a cool head and more managerial as a technical way to define what you expect from OpenStack and what you have to do. If you skip this step, you will literally drown yourself in the project overview on OpenStack. We have chosen this procedure. We are saddle and have agreed internally what we actually need OpenStack. Our motivation was not primarily to create a customer environment. However, we are not the seller of simple virtual servers in a mass scale. For our customers, we run complex applications from databases, load balancers, varnish, pacemaker clusters to web-based systems that are among the leading portals on the Slovak Internet. For this reason, our needs are directed internally for automation to simplify the management of our cloud environment. We want to know how to scale into the future and we do not want to limit it. The intention is to avoid errors in manual operations so that everything works reliably, easily, and accurately. And of course we want to have everything monitored by Zabbix.There''s our new OpenStack environment. Under the hood with Hyper-V and KVM. The network divides Neutron on VXLANs and Cinder is responsible for connecting our storage servers. And that''s just the beginning. In the next part of my blog, we will describe the different technologies and how we use them to offer you services under the Digmia - Expert Computing brand.</p>', '', NULL, NULL, '[]', '', '2018-12-04 14:16:22', 558, '', 558, '2018-12-05 19:42:00', '2018-12-04 16:32:29', 558, '2018-12-04 14:16:22', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1, 2, 1, 5, '', '', '', '', 1, '{"catItemTitle":"","catItemTitleLinked":"","catItemFeaturedNotice":"","catItemAuthor":"0","catItemDateCreated":"","catItemRating":"","catItemImage":"","catItemInt