(548, 51, 1, '', '2018-12-05 19:30:08', 558, 5885, '6f258339f5e7e796526d4994a4833f7aa714ae11', '{"id":51,"asset_id":312,"title":"IOT Business Hub","alias":"iot-bussiness-hub","introtext":"<h3>Your Business Performance Efficiency Tool<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>At present, commercial companies have already discovered the amazing added value of new technologies like IoT or Big Data Analysts. The incentives for using these technologies are opportunities that are already able to offer a strong added value for business. First, they enable our customers to save costs, thereby indirectly increasing profits. No less significant added value is to increase the efficiency of processes, where the technology used can help simplify processes or change them to bring added value either directly to the company or to its customers. IoT technology is to be understood only as a means of collecting valuable data about some business entities. In the second step, accurate data collection is supported by specialized data analysis based on the results of IoT devices. For analytical purposes and business optimization suggestions, we have dedicated ourselves to Big Data (for example, scientific research on a large amount of data). For a specific understanding of the use we can offer a solution for IoT technology for your business that we have developed to manage and route the data flow according to specific ideas and requirements of tailor-made customers.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>This project has already been implemented and deployed with our specific customer for thousands of devices. After designing the technical solution, we also help clients with the evaluation and processing of raw data in the form of structured feedback and detailed data analysis. The basic framework of applications that make up the IoT SW solution is as follows: The primary objective of the SW solution is to provide business partner data for business entities. the advantage of our solution is that it does not oblige the partner to use specific network technology. It even allows information about the same type of business entity to be delivered in parallel from different IoT networks (by coverage, convenience of contracts, etc.). solution it also allows information sent from different IoT transmitters of one IoT network to be registered to different partners. The SW solution consists of separate pre-integrated components that communicate through defined interfaces. The IOT Partner Business Hub application is intended to separate CRM (business functionality) from proprietary network communication - that is, allows you to attach business applications to so-called \\"Business API,\\" or connect a new network (network type) without affecting the business app.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The independence of business parts from the network provider and the specificity of the network technology used is achieved. In the case of upgrading or changes to support another network, it is enough to change the Partner Business Hub component. The basic entity in the Partner Business Hub is the IoT transmitter with its serial number (EUI) which uses the IoT network server to send messages. Messages such as signal strength, shipment time, receiving GTW, message size, unambiguous management identifier, and business information (generally a sensor or sensor state) in the base64 \\/ hexa format are metainformations. It is important to note that network management Typically, the business entity identifier does not have to be the absolute state of a business entity (for example, the state of a meter), and the business content of the message may not be a business entity identifier (customer, number of the meter, location number, etc.). For example, in the case of smart meters in utility companies, the number of pulses recorded by the sensor since it is mounted on the consumption meter - i.e., The application in its database contains mapping of IoT transmitters to a business entity, including the attributes needed to convert the sensor \\/ sensor state to relevant business information.<\\/p>","fulltext":"","state":1,"catid":"25","created":"2018-12-05 19:30:08","created_by":"558","created_by_alias":"","modified":"2018-12-05 19:30:08","modified_by":null,"checked_out":null,"checked_out_time":null,"publish_up":"2018-12-05 19:30:08","publish_down":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","images":"{\\"image_intro\\":\\"images\\\\\\/articles\\\\\\/eb6c7c01c4e98e1f2578f9959463b973.jpg\\",\\"float_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_caption\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"float_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_caption\\":\\"\\"}","urls":"{\\"urla\\":false,\\"urlatext\\":\\"\\",\\"targeta\\":\\"\\",\\"urlb\\":false,\\"urlbtext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetb\\":\\"\\",\\"urlc\\":false,\\"urlctext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetc\\":\\"\\"}","attribs":"{\\"article_layout\\":\\"\\",\\"show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"link_titles\\":\\"\\",\\"show_tags\\":\\"\\",\\"show_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_position\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"show_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_associations\\":\\"\\",\\"show_author\\":\\"\\",\\"link_author\\":\\"\\",\\"show_create_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_modify_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_publish_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_item_navigation\\":\\"\\",\\"show_icons\\":\\"\\",\\"show_print_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_email_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_vote\\":\\"\\",\\"show_hits\\":\\"\\",\\"show_noauth\\":\\"\\",\\"urls_position\\":\\"\\",\\"alternative_readmore\\":\\"\\",\\"article_page_title\\":\\"\\",\\"show_publishing_options\\":\\"\\",\\"show_article_options\\":\\"\\",\\"show_urls_images_backend\\":\\"\\",\\"show_urls_images_frontend\\":\\"\\",\\"spfeatured_image\\":\\"\\",\\"post_format\\":\\"standard\\",\\"gallery\\":\\"\\",\\"audio\\":\\"\\",\\"video\\":\\"\\",\\"link_title\\":\\"\\",\\"link_url\\":\\"\\",\\"quote_text\\":\\"\\",\\"quote_author\\":\\"\\",\\"post_status\\":\\"\\"}","version":1,"ordering":null,"metakey":"","metadesc":"","access":"1","hits":null,"metadata":"{\\"robots\\":\\"\\",\\"author\\":\\"\\",\\"rights\\":\\"\\",\\"xreference\\":\\"\\"}","featured":"0","language":"en-GB","xreference":"","note":""}', 0),
(549, 52, 1, '', '2018-12-05 19:31:18', 558, 8385, '1eaa26ea3f149ce7b97ee4eafdf8105f85c2645d', '{"id":52,"asset_id":313,"title":"Best Cloud Storage for Your Files","alias":"cloud-storage","introtext":"<p>Storage is never enough. Although we can easily expand the capacity of our computer with increasingly larger internal, external drives or USB keys, the more popular alternative today is the cloud that offers data independently of the platform and simple sharing capabilities, although in most cases at the expense of privacy. Unlike physical data carriers, the cloud offers multiple benefits. We do not have to worry about the data coming through the physical media error, but we have access to it from anywhere and from any device if we have a fast and stable internet connection. If circumstances so require, we can also download individual data to the device so we can access them even if we are not connected to the Internet. We have a choice from a wide portfolio of cloud solutions, and everyone can choose from their preferences. Almost every service offers a free version, but if we are interested in higher capacities, we do not avoid monthly charges.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>Dropbox<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>Dropbox is a fast-paced, cloud-based solution that is simplicity and reliability. He will also be pleased with its broad support and the ability to install an application on all popular operating systems, whether on computers or smartphones. Applications are very well-crafted, clear, and easy to share files quickly. The company has also recently launched the Paper Service to create notes or documents, and is directly linked to Dropbox. The main drawback of Dropbox is the small storage size in the free version. If you do not want to pay, count only 2 GB of space. For 9.99 euros per month or 99 euros a year, you can subscribe to 1 TB of free space. The company also offers solutions for teams where it is possible to get from 15 euros per month unlimited space. However, it is necessary to expect that the data is stored in the United States and unencrypted.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>Google Drive<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>If you already have a Google Account, you have access to the Google Drive cloud automatically. As a Google product, Drive is strongly integrated with most of Google''s services. Google Docs created in Sheets, Docs, Slides are all centrally available on Drive Drive, making it easy for the user to manage and share them. You can also easily save attachments from Gmail and enjoy the integration of Google Photos. Drive shares its storage with Gmail and data from your Google Photos, so the available capacity is shared between all services. In the free version Google offers 15 GB of space for your files. If you are 15GB a little, but you do not need the whole terabyte at the same time, there is the possibility to subscribe to a 100GB storage for 1.99 euros per month or, respectively, 19.99 for advance payment for the whole year. One TB space costs \\u20ac 9.99 per month or \\u20ac 99.99 per year. The most you can subscribe to 30 TB for EUR 299.99 per month. Of course, Windows, MacOS as well as Android and iOS applications are commonplace. Even in this case, the data is stored in the US and unencrypted.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>OneDrive &lt; \\/ h3&gt;<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>Microsoft software giant also offers custom software storage. OneDrive is part of the latest Windows 10 operating system, but the native application is also available for OSX and Windows Phone, Android, and iOS mobile platforms. OneDrive is a good choice if you also prefer other Microsoft products as it does not have a good connection with the cloud office suite MS Office 365. Based on Microsoft, it offers 5 GB of free storage, and for 2 euros a month it is possible to subscribe to 50 GB of cloud space. There is also no option to subscribe to 1 TB solution for 7 euros per month or more. 69 eur per year, with the MS Office 365 service license included in this package. Again, data is stored in the US and unencrypted.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>iCloud<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>Apple platform users have the option to use iCloud, which is directly integrated into macOS and iOS. The advantage of iCloud is especially true if you own multiple devices from Apple and you can easily synchronize data between them through iCloud. Compatibility with other platforms is all the worse. Apple has 5 GB of storage for free use and 99GB a month for 50GB of storage. Next is 200GB for 2.99 euros per month and 2TB for 9.99 euros per month. Data is stored in the US and only a part is encrypted.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>Mega<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>For those who want the largest storage in the free version, Mega is the right service for Kim Dotcom, the author of the controversial canceled Megaupload service. In the free version, the Mega user offers up to 50GB of data. The service does not lack rich sync capabilities, the Windows, MacOS and Linux apps as well as the mobile operating system versions. You can also use Meg as an extension for Chrome and Firefox. Mega is the only service in this article that has data encrypted on your servers with keys that you only have as owners of the data. The Mega service does not know what data you have in the cloud and can be considered the only one that does not disturb your privacy. If you do not have enough 50 GB, you can buy 200 GB of space per month at a price of 4.99 euros, with 1 TB worth the same competition of 9.99 euros. There are also 4 and 8 TB spaces in the menu.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>box<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>The Cloud Storage Box tries to target mainly businesses and business users, but it can also appeal to individuals. The service also offers applications for all major operating systems, and will also be pleased with integration with many other services and applications. The box also gives the user a lot of privacy control. Free storage offers the user 10GB of space, and for 8euro per month, it is possible to subscribe to 100GB, which is somewhat higher compared to the competitor.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>Custom Cloud<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>One option is also to set up your own cloud. For example, solutions from Synology are popular. Just buy a NAS with the disk capacity you prefer, and you no longer pay for it, as is the case with standard cloud services. The advantage of your own solution is that you know where your data is and you have privacy. Even home solutions do not have access to multiple devices or automatic backup of photos, and we can also find similarities to Sheets, Docs, or more. To some extent, there is no connection with the cloud of well-known players in the market.<\\/p>","fulltext":"","state":1,"catid":"25","created":"2018-12-05 19:31:18","created_by":"558","created_by_alias":"","modified":"2018-12-05 19:31:18","modified_by":null,"checked_out":null,"checked_out_time":null,"publish_up":"2018-12-05 19:31:18","publish_down":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","images":"{\\"image_intro\\":\\"images\\\\\\/articles\\\\\\/37a06e4a72d6cb27621f1ed829bbee81.jpg\\",\\"float_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_caption\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"float_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_caption\\":\\"\\"}","urls":"{\\"urla\\":false,\\"urlatext\\":\\"\\",\\"targeta\\":\\"\\",\\"urlb\\":false,\\"urlbtext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetb\\":\\"\\",\\"urlc\\":false,\\"urlctext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetc\\":\\"\\"}","attribs":"{\\"article_layout\\":\\"\\",\\"show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"link_titles\\":\\"\\",\\"show_tags\\":\\"\\",\\"show_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_position\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"show_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_associations\\":\\"\\",\\"show_author\\":\\"\\",\\"link_author\\":\\"\\",\\"show_create_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_modify_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_publish_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_item_navigation\\":\\"\\",\\"show_icons\\":\\"\\",\\"show_print_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_email_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_vote\\":\\"\