(556, 50, 1, '', '2018-12-05 19:39:38', 558, 9138, 'caaaf27498480e7d735f8389c7f4f0860c4886be', '{"id":50,"asset_id":"311","title":"Important changes to GDPR privacy","alias":"important-changes-to-gdpr-privacy","introtext":"<p><em> The new European Privacy Policy (GDPR) <em> has been in force since May 25, 2018. It brings a number of changes, including, in particular, testing online security environments or empowering people responsible for managing personal data.<\\/em><\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>consent to processing of personal data<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>If you own a website, an e-shop, or you are making an online questionnaire, you will surely have a check box to agree with the handling of personal information. Such a pre-checked consent will no longer be valid. With new processing of personal data, you will need to ask for new approvals. We also agree with the processing of your children''s personal data. For children under the age of 16, only the parent or their legal representative may grant consent. The new regulation specifies the terms of consent:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li>consent must be free, specific, informed, and unambiguous<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>consent must be given for a specific purpose, for each purpose, each must be named<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Acknowledgment must be as easy as giving consent\\r\\n<h3 p=\\"\\">Expand and refine the rights of individuals to better control personal data. These include, for example, the right to:<\\/h3>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li>information<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>access to personal information<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>patch<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Erase \\/ Forget - This right follows on from the older \\"right to erase\\". For example, an individual may apply it if the data is unlawfully processed or has opted out of consent to the processing of personal data.\\r\\n<p><em> \\"Clients will have the right to delete or move personal data from your database.\\"<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li>Right to Restrict Processing<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Right to data portability - The person concerned will have the right to transfer his \\/ her personal data to another operator. The original operator is required to provide this data in the normal format. An example is the change of the mobile operator. If the user decides to transfer his number to another operator after May 25, 2018, the original operator must provide the new operator of the user with personal data (their type directly governed by the Regulation) associated with the use of his services during the provision of the service.<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Right to object<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Right to object profiling\\r\\n<h3>Safety precautions<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>When processing personal data, you are responsible for their security against cyber attacks. Your obligation will take reasonable precautions, for example:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li>pseudonymization<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>encryption<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Ensure the continued confidentiality, integrity and availability of systems \\/ services<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Ability to restore the availability of personal data in the event of an incident in time\\r\\n<h3>Regular security testing<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>An important security measure will also be regular testing and assessment of the effectiveness of the security measures taken to ensure data processing security (eg <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/citadelo.sk\\/sluzby\\/audity-bezpecnosti\\/\\"> Penetration Tests <\\/a> &gt;, <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/hacktrophy.com\\/preco-je-dolezity-bug-bounty-program-pre-stredne-firmy\\/\\"> bug bounty programs <\\/a>). This measure also includes checking the security of the application or site through which personal data flows. For companies, it means they have to pay attention to how they have a coded site and whether it does not contain security holes through which it can be hacked and stolen. <em> If you do not know if your site or mobile app is safe enough, test it with ethical hackers from <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/citadelo.com\\/\\"> Citadelo <\\/a> or &lt; a href = \\"https:\\/\\/hacktrophy.com\\/\\"&gt; <em> hacktrophy.com <em>.<\\/em><\\/em><\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>Documentation<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>Once you are new, you must comply with the protection of personal data. It is your duty to show how this requirement is complied with. Therefore, it is essential to have the necessary documentation available, for example:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li>internal guidelines (attendance, file handling, incident identification, camera system, e-mail, backup)<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>documenting the security measures taken<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>staff training on personal data processing obligations\\r\\n<h3>Notification obligation introduced<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>Each operator and intermediary will be obliged to report any incident, ie a breach of personal data protection, within 72 hours of the Office of Personal Data Protection of the Slovak Republic. In the event of an incident and possible theft of personal data, he will be obliged to report the incident to the person concerned. Another change is the obligation to document cases of personal data breach and the need to submit them to the Office upon request. Everyone who processes personal information should answer the following questions:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li>Can you detect an incident and a privacy violation early?<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Can you properly and timely evaluate the incident, its consequences and take action?\\r\\n<h3>Will a person be responsible?<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>If you process a large amount of personal data or are sensitive data, you are definitely responsible (may be a legal entity). We surely recommend that you:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li>have an internal analysis of whether or not the responsible person should be named and show that you have taken all relevant factors into account<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>entrusted within your organization with a person who will have privacy protection \\"in the job description\\"\\r\\n<p>For violation of GDPR''s obligations, a fine of up to \\u20ac 20 million or 4% of total turnover for the previous financial year (whichever is greater) is a penalty. Likewise, any person who has suffered harm as a result of a violation of the Regulation is entitled to compensation. The application of the new GDPR Regulation thus significantly increases the demand for Slovak and Czech companies. Companies are under new obligation to test the security of online systems through which personal data is moving. Companies should have an overview of the flow of personal data and periodically review, assess and evaluate the effectiveness and appropriateness of the security measures that are taken.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3 ul=\\"\\"><\\/h3>\\r\\n<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Identify which personal data you have \\/ process in your business, and whether you process it legally and for the purpose for which it was obtained.<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Answer the question which data you really need; Do not delete and delete unnecessary data.<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Identify the flow of personal information in your organization - how and where it is stored, protected or deleted, and who has access to it.\\r\\n<h3>Are you ready?<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>Prepare legal, personnel and technical conditions for implementing the regulation can be challenging for many companies. So do not hesitate to contact external companies that are working on the issue and delegate these tasks to them.<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","fulltext":"","state":1,"catid":"25","created":"2018-12-05 19:29:15","created_by":"558","created_by_alias":"","modified":"2018-12-05 19:39:38","modified_by":"558","checked_out":"558","checked_out_time":"2018-12-05 19:37:31","publish_up":"2018-12-05 19:29:15","publish_down":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","images":"{\\"image_intro\\":\\"images\\\\\\/articles\\\\\\/ccb4e23c8aa216f1e96d31ab209c036b.jpg\\",\\"float_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_caption\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"float_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_caption\\":\\"\\"}","urls":"{\\"urla\\":false,\\"urlatext\\":\\"\\",\\"targeta\\":\\"\\",\\"urlb\\":false,\\"urlbtext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetb\\":\\"\\",\\"urlc\\":false,\\"urlctext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetc\\":\\"\\"}","attribs":"{\\"article_layout\\":\\"\\",\\"show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"link_titles\\":\\"\\",\\"show_tags\\":\\"\\",\\"show_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_position\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"show_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_associations\\":\\"\\",\\"show_author\\":\\"\\",\\"link_author\\":\\"\\",\\"show_create_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_modify_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_publish_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_item_navigation\\":\\"\\",\\"show_icons\\":\\"\\",\\"show_print_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_email_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_vote\\":\\"\\",\\"show_hits\\":\\"\\",\\"show_noauth\\":\\"\\",\\"urls_position\\":\\"\\",\\"alternative_readmore\\":\\"\\",\\"article_page_title\\":\\"\\",\\"show_publishing_options\\":\\"\\",\\"show_article_options\\":\\"\\",\\"show_urls_images_backend\\":\\"\\",\\"show_urls_images_frontend\\":\\"\\",\\"spfeatured_image\\":\\"\\",\\"post_format\\":\\"standard\\",\\"gallery\\":\\"\\",\\"audio\\":\\"\\",\\"video\\":\\"\\",\\"link_title\\":\\"\\",\\"link_url\\":\\"\\",\\"quote_text\\":\\"\\",\\"quote_author\\":\\"\\",\\"post_status\\":\\"\\"}","version":2,"ordering":"3","metakey":"","metadesc":"","access":"1","hits":"0","metadata":"{\\"robots\\":\\"\\",\\"author\\":\\"\\",\\"rights\\":\\"\\",\\"xreference\\":\\"\\"}","featured":"0","language":"en-GB","xreference":"","note":""}', 0),
(557, 55, 1, '', '2018-12-05 19:39:51', 558, 5073, 'b331b0470229f535abae1e9ef4ee6fe295c47371', '{"id":55,"asset_id":"316","title":"Custom IT Infrastructure or Cloud Solution - How to Choose?","alias":"custom-it-infrastructure","introtext":"<p>Every medium or large business must ask the question: \\"Is my application a product running on a suitable platform?\\" Therefore, we would like to bring you closer to the basic differences between the solutions available, their advantages and strengths, and help in deciding .<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>1. Custom physical servers, \\"Bare metal\\"<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>Own physical servers, care for them, configure, pay for housing, electricity and the whole environment to manage and monitor is a horrific idea for small and medium businesses. The solution may be the contractor''s \\/ manager''s contract, which is the most costly among the options offered. When does Bare Metal have a meaning? Reasons are for some of those services that can only be operated by a service serviced from a bare metal platform. This is mainly about the security of the entire solution that no one has access to except the server and customer manager. For the sake of maintaining their own physical servers, the GDPR regulation, the legislation, and the contractual requirements of customers that restrict the storage of data outside the EU or shared infrastructure may be. All of these parameters affect the choice of a suitable solution.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>2. Private cloud<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>The essence of providing a private cloud is to create a custom-tailored environment for customers where the customer is as far as possible separated from the physical platform on which his product is running. The benefits of a private cloud are the effort to compete with the public cloud while offering the customer something extra. Customers will also appreciate support from technically sophisticated vendor administrators who can help you troubleshoot application problems, fine-tune the database environment, or advise on technical product implementation issues.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>3. Public Cloud<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>The benefits are in clearly defined rules, so if something is done on this platform, you can do it almost instantly with a few mouse clicks in the cloud web user interface. But that is also a disadvantage. If a customer has a problem and can not technically be solved by bending the resources defined by the provider through his web interface, the customer must customize their product.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>If you''re dynamic and impatient, you need everything and right now, so just what some public cloud provides. If you already have a product that you offer and actively develop and do not meet major provider limitations or want to benefit from the collaboration of administrators, developers, and you do not want to pay unnecessarily for managing your own hardware, the choice is a private cloud. If you deal with sensitive data, you require a high level of security or that legislation requires that your own physical server is the solution I am looking for. We recommend, but before this change consult with Digmia experts and arrange a free consultation where you will advise which solution is for you most suitable.<\\/p>","fulltext":"","state":1,"catid":"23","created":"2018-12-05 19:34:17","created_by":"558","created_by_alias":"","modified":"2018-12-05 19:39:51","modified_by":"558","checked_out":"558","checked_out_time":"2018-12-05 19:37:38","publish_up":"2018-12-05 19:34:17","publish_down":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","images":"{\\"image_intro\\":\\"images\\\\\\/articles\\\\\\/620466077c427f141effa294382f5fba.jpg\\",\\"float_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_caption\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"float_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_caption\\":\\"\\"}","urls":"{\\"urla\\":false,\\"urlatext\\":\\"\\",\\"targeta\\":\\"\\",\\"urlb\\":false,\\"urlbtext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetb\\":\\"\\",\\"urlc\\":false,\\"urlctext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetc\\":\\"\\"}","attribs":"{\\"article_layout\\":\\"\\",\\"show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"link_titles\\":\\"\\",\\"show_tags\\":\\"\\",\\"show_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_position\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"show_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_associations\\":\\"\\",\\"show_author\\":\\"\\",\\"link_author\\":\\"\\",\\"show_create_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_modify_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_publish_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_item_navigation\\":\\"\\",\\"show_icons\\":\\"\\",\\"show_print_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_email_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_vote\\":\\"\\",\\"show_hits\\":\\"\\",\\"show_noauth\\":\\"\\",\\"urls_position\\":\\"\\",\\"alternative_readmore\\":\\"\\",\\"article_page_title\\":\\"\\",\\"show_publishing_options\\":\\"\\",\\"show_article_options\\":\\"\\",\\"show_urls_images_backend\\":\\"\\",\\"show_urls_images_frontend\\":\\"\\",\\"spfeatured_image\\":\\"\\",\\"post_format\\":\\"standard\\",\\"gallery\\":\\"\\",\\"audio\\":\\"\\",\\"video\\":\\"\\",\\"link_title\\":\\"\\",\\"link_url\\":\\"\\",\\"quote_text\\":\\"\\",\\"quote_author\\":\\"\\",\\"post_status\\":\\"\\"}","version":2,"ordering":"2","metakey":"","metadesc":"","access":"1","hits":"0","metadata":"{\\"robots\\":\\"\\",\\"author\\":\\"\\",\\"rights\\":\\"\\",\\"xreference\\":\\"\\"}","featured":"0","language":"en-GB","xreference":"","note":""}', 0),
(558, 53, 1, '', '2018-12-05 19:40:16', 558, 8682, '8cfe825564ce399911e674206bb6241ceff377f1', '{"id":53,"asset_id":"314","title":"How to prepare for GDPR?","alias":"how-to-prepare-for-gdpr","introtext":"<p>Peter Fuska, CEO of Digmia, about what will bring the new GDPR regulation to individuals and businesses, what does that mean in practice and how companies can prepare for it. Please read the interview or watch the video.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>What changes does the new OU do for businesses? h3&gt;<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>The new EU Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) enters into force uniformly throughout the EU on 25 May 2018. The Regulation provides for increased protection of individuals in the processing of personal data, in particular by entrepreneurs and public administrations and self-governments. For natural persons, this extends the scope of the rights they may apply to the processing of personal data, such as the right to transfer personal data, the limitation of processing or the complete deletion of personal data. Similarly, entrepreneurs and institutions (whether in the position of an operator or an intermediary) introduce obligations that an entrepreneur has to meet if a natural person wants to exercise his rights in the area of \\u200b\\u200bpersonal data protection.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>What specific principles or principles of protection the OU brings and what does it mean in practice?<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>The Regulation defines eight principles that will govern the processing of personal data of the individuals concerned. I will only mention the key: the principle of legality and purpose limitations, we can obtain personal information only for a specific purpose and process it only in a way that is compatible for that purpose. For the purpose of defining the purpose, the entrepreneur has either support in other laws (eg the Social \\/ Health Insurance Act when collecting OU when reporting a worker to a social or health insurance company) or processing necessary for performance of the contract or for pre-contractual arrangements (eg when buying a holiday or tickets) or there is a legitimate interest of the businessman in processing (eg, the protection of his \\/ her own property when entering the premises). Of course, personal data can be processed based on the consent of the natural person, which in many cases will be the only legal solution. The principle of minimization in terms of the extent and duration of the retention of personal data, the entrepreneur has to check, for example, for the purpose of the selection process, only collects the data relevant for decision-making on candidates and will not be able to keep the resumes of unsuccessful candidates for a long time after the selection and occupation of the position (many managers will find such CVs in their emails or folders). The principle of integrity and confidentiality, the entrepreneur must have adequate technical means and measures in place to ensure the security of personal data and to prevent unauthorized access, damage or loss of personal data.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>There is a fairly wide range of technical means, I would certainly start with areas where there is a high level of vulnerability - PC protection, especially laptops, that workers normally transfer between work and home. Introducing disk encryption on your laptop is key to data protection in case of theft. It is also important to protect data in the electronic data transfer between company headquarters and external parties - transmission via an encrypted VPN tunnel as a necessity for personal data to be captured and misused. Managing employee access to personal data is particularly important in minimizing personal data misuse inside the company. It is recommended to introduce a 2-factor authentication that requires additional authentication of the person accessing personal data (eg token) in addition to logins and passwords.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>. to lose or steal personal data, what steps do you need on the operator side?<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>At first it is important to judge how high the likelihood that theft, the laptop will lead to a high risk from the point of view of the rights of the individuals concerned. If a doctor stole a notebook with an unencrypted disk that has sensitive patient health data, the risk is high and the operator is required to report an incident to the Office for Personal Data Protection within 72 hours of its occurrence. It is also necessary to inform the affected person of such breach \\/ incidents. In order to communicate with the Authority and the persons concerned, it is appropriate to have a so- responsible person. However, not every operator must necessarily have such a person - it concerns, for example, public authorities or processors who process specific categories of data such as genetic, biometric, health, and so on.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>The new Regulation enters into force on 25 May 2018. How are entrepreneurs and institutions prepared and what do you need to do to comply with this regulation?<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>Many, in particular, small and medium-sized businesses have been convinced that the regulation does not concern them, or they intervene very marginally, and that''s why they did not get them. However, when we realize that personal data is most often a part of customer and employee data (every entrepreneur has customers and the vast majority also employs individuals), the regulation can not be avoided. In terms of readiness, most entrepreneurs are in the first - analytical phase in which they identify where processes \\/ functional areas are or are not in line with the Regulation. The part (rather minority) has a ready-made implementation plan and has begun introducing measures for critical areas. To achieve compliance, each processor should have at least three basic steps:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li>Perform a so-called GAP analysis, i. view your business processes, map your personal data flowing through the organization, and assess where the areas do not meet the requirements of the regulation (eg to assess or have a purpose for collecting and processing personal data)<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Prepare a draft measure, evaluate it in terms of cost and time, and create an implementation plan<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Run the implementation of steps that can cover the areas of: o Technical (IT) - encryption, pseudonymization, 2-factor authentication and others o Organizational - change of scope of collected personal data in processes, modifications in the entitlements of personnel processing personal data or change physical access to premises where sensitive personal information is processed. o Legal and documentation - preparation of texts for consent to the processing of personal data, preparation and signing of processing contracts with business partners, eventually introducing a code of conduct, etc.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>","fulltext":"","state":1,"catid":"25","created":"2018-12-05 19:32:16","created_by":"558","created_by_alias":"","modified":"2018-12-05 19:40:16","modified_by":"558","checked_out":"558","checked_out_time":"2018-12-05 19:40:00","publish_up":"2018-12-05 19:32:16","publish_down":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","images":"{\\"image_intro\\":\\"images\\\\\\/articles\\\\\\/542390225756f78888142d54f3d17e01.jpg\\",\\"float_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_caption\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"float_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_caption\\":\\"\\"}","urls":"{\\"urla\\":false,\\"urlatext\\":\\"\\",\\"targeta\\":\\"\\",\\"urlb\\":false,\\"urlbtext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetb\\":\\"\\",\\"urlc\\":false,\\"urlctext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetc\\":\\"\\"}","attribs":"{\\"article_layout\\":\\"\\",\\"show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"link_titles\\":\\"\\",\\"show_tags\\":\\"\\",\\"show_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_position\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"show_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_associations\\":\\"\\",\\"show_author\\":\\"\\",\\"link_author\\":\\"\\",\\"show_create_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_modify_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_publish_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_item_navigation\\":\\"\\",\\"show_icons\\":\\"\\",\\"show_print_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_email_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_vote\\":\\"\\",\\"show_hits\\":\\"\\",\\"show_noauth\\":\\"\\",\\"urls_position\\":\\"\\",\\"alternative_readmore\\":\\"\\",\\"article_page_title\\":\\"\\",\\"show_publishing_options\\":\\"\\",\\"show_article_options\\":\\"\\",\\"show_urls_images_backend\\":\\"\\",\\"show_urls_images_frontend\\":\\"\\",\\"spfeatured_image\\":\\"\\",\\"post_format\\":\\"standard\\",\\"gallery\\":\\"\\",\\"audio\\":\\"\\",\\"video\\":\\"\\",\\"link_title\\":\\"\\",\\"link_url\\":\\"\\",\\"quote_text\\":\\"\\",\\"quote_author\\":\\"\\",\\"post_status\\":\\"\\"}","version":2,"ordering":"0","metakey":"","metadesc":"","access":"1","hits":"0","metadata":"{\\"robots\\":\\"\\",\\"author\\":\\"\\",\\"rights\\":\\"\\",\\"xreference\\":\\"\\"}","featured":"0","language":"en-GB","xreference":"","note":""}', 0),
(559, 56, 1, '', '2018-12-05 19:40:41', 558, 6932, 'd6ef4e8031ca25da6fc2010de118417c36797fb9', '{"id":56,"asset_id":"317","title":"Server operation is not a commodity","alias":"server-operation-is-not-a-commodity","introtext":"<p>Many developers consider hosting and server as commodities. It''s something they buy from a datacenter company or different forms of virtualization or platforms as services. Business owners are similar to electricity or other utilities - servers work, do not need to do it, and get an account for them. It is true that server infrastructure, whether in real or virtual form, is becoming more and more simple to operate. Clients, however, often encounter unoccupied space that is not completely under control. The operator can deliver a great added value in this direction, which saves a lot of costs, but especially stress on all sides. Is the fact that the operator has launched several dozen applications that were most likely to have even higher performance and availability requirements? Is it worthwhile to cooperate with a company that can keep applications running for years and not \\"get in touch\\" with technological developments, just the opposite, and improve on the operating site?<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Scalability, redundancy, and performance are often marginalized in the development of applications or are only addressed at the last minute. When fine-tuning the application that is not ready for sharp operation, it is rarely necessary to spend up to a dozen additional human readings. The developer''s priority is to deliver a functional application that meets the customer''s requirements. After uploading, however, everything does not always work the way it is written in the documentation. However, the responsible developer can avoid potential problems with a brief discussion with the application operator on scaling, redundancy and performance. For example, a weighty task, often overlooked, is a key task. They help uncover the tight throat and predict when the infrastructure will need to be restored. Infrastructure scaling is often \\"intuitive\\" when estimated performance is estimated based on the expected number of users based on past experience. When it comes to estimating, it is difficult to reveal a narrow throat that can be in the application - if the application is not tested under a lot of load, it is very likely that the power is under-shot or cracked. But there is also the question of scalability - if I add another server, will it help? Applications often do not run linearly, which means that doubling the number of servers does not have to double the number of customers the client can serve. There may even be a narrow throat when adding more power will not help any more. Do you know how your app scrolls?<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>Development, testing and documentation<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>Another common problem is that developers do not provide documentation for the application. We call it \\"It works on my laptop!\\" Developer has its own development environment where the application tests it during development. It then sends the hosting company or the \\"finished product\\" platform, and the deployment expert determines the configuration of the server, which modules of the application framework and its application works. The developer''s response is always about the specific problem of why the application does not work, install ImageMagick, \\"and it is not clear to the developer whether the application has functional requirements for running. However, this is important in terms of operation, not only for the initial startup but also for possible upgrades of the infrastructure, operating system, application server, etc. To solve this problem, it is good to take two steps: Have a specific test environment that resembles as much as possible the production environment (and it''s not a developer''s notebook or a \\"server\\" in the kitchen below the table). This test environment is good to maintain and test any changes on the production platform. In the test environment, we can also test new versions of packages and security patches. The second step is to get developers to upload the application with up-to-date installation and operating documentation.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>DIGMIA has been working on systems for a long time - this year we celebrated our 10th birthday! We run large Slovak and foreign portals, critical business systems across industries, or network infrastructure for demanding customers, such as terrestrial broadcasting. With our sophisticated monitoring and non-stop hotline, our customer''s applications work faster and more cost-effectively. Our unique experienced experts have access to the latest technologies and knowledge. In addition, we love open-source software, we also contribute to its development and we prefer it to client solutions. And we also enjoy working with developers. Our extensive experience in deploying operations and scalable redundant server farms can save them a lot of work and worries. And ultimately, the most important satisfied customer is the one who works.<\\/p>","fulltext":"","state":1,"catid":"23","created":"2018-12-05 19:35:22","created_by":"558","created_by_alias":"","modified":"2018-12-05 19:40:41","modified_by":"558","checked_out":"558","checked_out_time":"2018-12-05 19:40:06","publish_up":"2018-12-05 19:35:22","publish_down":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","images":"{\\"image_intro\\":\\"images\\\\\\/articles\\\\\\/a522a6005d1cb428ea34ef1769cd7452.jpg\\",\\"float_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_caption\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"float_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_caption\\":\\"\\"}","urls":"{\\"urla\\":false,\\"urlatext\\":\\"\\",\\"targeta\\":\\"\\",\\"urlb\\":false,\\"urlbtext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetb\\":\\"\\",\\"urlc\\":false,\\"urlctext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetc\\":\\"\\"}","attribs":"{\\"article_layout\\":\\"\\",\\"show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"link_titles\\":\\"\\",\\"show_tags\\":\\"\\",\\"show_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_position\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"show_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_associations\\":\\"\\",\\"show_author\\":\\"\\",\\"link_author\\":\\"\\",\\"show_create_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_modify_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_publish_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_item_navigation\\":\\"\\",\\"show_icons\\":\\"\\",\\"show_print_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_email_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_vote\\":\\"\\",\\"show_hits\\":\\"\\",\\"show_noauth\\":\\"\\",\\"urls_position\\":\\"\\",\\"alternative_readmore\\":\\"\\",\\"article_page_title\\":\\"\\",\\"show_publishing_options\\":\\"\\",\\"show_article_options\\":\\"\\",\\"show_urls_images_backend\\":\\"\\",\\"show_urls_images_frontend\\":\\"\\",\\"spfeatured_image\\":\\"\\",\\"post_format\\":\\"standard\\",\\"gallery\\":\\"\\",\\"audio\\":\\"\\",\\"video\\":\\"\\",\\"link_title\\":\\"\\",\\"link_url\\":\\"\\",\\"quote_text\\":\\"\\",\\"quote_author\\":\\"\\",\\"post_status\\":\\"\\"}","version":2,"ordering":"1","metakey":"","metadesc":"","access":"1","hits":"0","metadata":"{\\"robots\\":\\"\\",\\"author\\":\\"\\",\\"rights\\":\\"\\",\\"xreference\\":\\"\\"}","featured":"0","language":"en-GB","xreference":"","note":""}', 0),
(560, 52, 1, '', '2018-12-05 19:44:55', 558, 8389, 'd8168d0ea3473fb1ce6891486aa53291a7bf9e99', '{"id":52,"asset_id":"313","title":"Best Cloud Storage for Your Files","alias":"cloud-storage","introtext":"<p>Storage is never enough. Although we can easily expand the capacity of our computer with increasingly larger internal, external drives or USB keys, the more popular alternative today is the cloud that offers data independently of the platform and simple sharing capabilities, although in most cases at the expense of privacy. Unlike physical data carriers, the cloud offers multiple benefits. We do not have to worry about the data coming through the physical media error, but we have access to it from anywhere and from any device if we have a fast and stable internet connection. If circumstances so require, we can also download individual data to the device so we can access them even if we are not connected to the Internet. We have a choice from a wide portfolio of cloud solutions, and everyone can choose from their preferences. Almost every service offers a free version, but if we are interested in higher capacities, we do not avoid monthly charges.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>Dropbox<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>Dropbox is a fast-paced, cloud-based solution that is simplicity and reliability. He will also be pleased with its broad support and the ability to install an application on all popular operating systems, whether on computers or smartphones. Applications are very well-crafted, clear, and easy to share files quickly. The company has also recently launched the Paper Service to create notes or documents, and is directly linked to Dropbox. The main drawback of Dropbox is the small storage size in the free version. If you do not want to pay, count only 2 GB of space. For 9.99 euros per month or 99 euros a year, you can subscribe to 1 TB of free space. The company also offers solutions for teams where it is possible to get from 15 euros per month unlimited space. However, it is necessary to expect that the data is stored in the United States and unencrypted.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>Google Drive<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>If you already have a Google Account, you have access to the Google Drive cloud automatically. As a Google product, Drive is strongly integrated with most of Google''s services. Google Docs created in Sheets, Docs, Slides are all centrally available on Drive Drive, making it easy for the user to manage and share them. You can also easily save attachments from Gmail and enjoy the integration of Google Photos. Drive shares its storage with Gmail and data from your Google Photos, so the available capacity is shared between all services. In the free version Google offers 15 GB of space for your files. If you are 15GB a little, but you do not need the whole terabyte at the same time, there is the possibility to subscribe to a 100GB storage for 1.99 euros per month or, respectively, 19.99 for advance payment for the whole year. One TB space costs \\u20ac 9.99 per month or \\u20ac 99.99 per year. The most you can subscribe to 30 TB for EUR 299.99 per month. Of course, Windows, MacOS as well as Android and iOS applications are commonplace. Even in this case, the data is stored in the US and unencrypted.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>OneDrive<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>Microsoft software giant also offers custom software storage. OneDrive is part of the latest Windows 10 operating system, but the native application is also available for OSX and Windows Phone, Android, and iOS mobile platforms. OneDrive is a good choice if you also prefer other Microsoft products as it does not have a good connection with the cloud office suite MS Office 365. Based on Microsoft, it offers 5 GB of free storage, and for 2 euros a month it is possible to subscribe to 50 GB of cloud space. There is also no option to subscribe to 1 TB solution for 7 euros per month or more. 69 eur per year, with the MS Office 365 service license included in this package. Again, data is stored in the US and unencrypted.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>iCloud<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>Apple platform users have the option to use iCloud, which is directly integrated into macOS and iOS. The advantage of iCloud is especially true if you own multiple devices from Apple and you can easily synchronize data between them through iCloud. Compatibility with other platforms is all the worse. Apple has 5 GB of storage for free use and 99GB a month for 50GB of storage. Next is 200GB for 2.99 euros per month and 2TB for 9.99 euros per month. Data is stored in the US and only a part is encrypted.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>Mega<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>For those who want the largest storage in the free version, Mega is the right service for Kim Dotcom, the author of the controversial canceled Megaupload service. In the free version, the Mega user offers up to 50GB of data. The service does not lack rich sync capabilities, the Windows, MacOS and Linux apps as well as the mobile operating system versions. You can also use Meg as an extension for Chrome and Firefox. Mega is the only service in this article that has data encrypted on your servers with keys that you only have as owners of the data. The Mega service does not know what data you have in the cloud and can be considered the only one that does not disturb your privacy. If you do not have enough 50 GB, you can buy 200 GB of space per month at a price of 4.99 euros, with 1 TB worth the same competition of 9.99 euros. There are also 4 and 8 TB spaces in the menu.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>box<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>The Cloud Storage Box tries to target mainly businesses and business users, but it can also appeal to individuals. The service also offers applications for all major operating systems, and will also be pleased with integration with many other services and applications. The box also gives the user a lot of privacy control. Free storage offers the user 10GB of space, and for 8euro per month, it is possible to subscribe to 100GB, which is somewhat higher compared to the competitor.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>Custom Cloud<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>One option is also to set up your own cloud. For example, solutions from Synology are popular. Just buy a NAS with the disk capacity you prefer, and you no longer pay for it, as is the case with standard cloud services. The advantage of your own solution is that you know where your data is and you have privacy. Even home solutions do not have access to multiple devices or automatic backup of photos, and we can also find similarities to Sheets, Docs, or more. To some extent, there is no connection with the cloud of well-known players in the market.<\\/p>","fulltext":"","state":1,"catid":"25","created":"2018-12-05 19:31:18","created_by":"558","created_by_alias":"","modified":"2018-12-05 19:44:55","modified_by":"558","checked_out":"558","checked_out_time":"2018-12-05 19:44:46","publish_up":"2018-12-05 19:31:18","publish_down":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","images":"{\\"image_intro\\":\\"images\\\\\\/articles\\\\\\/37a06e4a72d6cb27621f1ed829bbee81.jpg\\",\\"float_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_caption\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"float_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_caption\\":\\"\\"}","urls":"{\\"urla\\":false,\\"urlatext\\":\\"\\",\\"targeta\\":\\"\\",\\"urlb\\":false,\\"urlbtext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetb\\":\\"\\",\\"urlc\\":false,\\"urlctext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetc\\":\\"\\"}","attribs":"{\\"article_layout\\":\\"\\",\\"show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"link_titles\\":\\"\\",\\"show_tags\\":\\"\\",\\"show_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_position\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"show_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_associations\\":\\"\\",\\"show_author\\":\\"\\",\\"link_author\\":\\"\\",\\"show_create_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_modify_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_publish_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_item_navigation\\":\\"\\",\\"show_icons\\":\\"\\",\\"show_print_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_email_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_vote\\"